CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F361A1778191867
OL,3,CYorkshire Labour MPs brace for painful
OL,4,Clocal election results
OL,6,FThe Liberal Democrats face a tricky
OL,7,Fbattle to keep control of Hull City
OL,8,FCouncil, which sources say is shaping
OL,9,Fup to be a straight fight with Reform,
OL,10,Fsimilar to the mayoral election which
OL,11,FNigel Farage's party won.
OL,13,FBecause only a third of seats are up
OL,14,Ffor grabs, Reform will not win a
OL,15,Fmajority in Hull but they could
OL,16,Finflict serious damage on both the Lib
OL,17,FDems and Labour.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G6/8
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,362,360,260,120,000,100
PN,36107
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F361A1778191867
OL,3,CYorkshire Labour MPs brace for painful
OL,4,Clocal election results
OL,6,FMeanwhile, in North East Lincolnshire
OL,7,Fthe Conservatives are hoping to hang
OL,8,Fon, but again face a tough challenge
OL,9,Fconsidering their position in the
OL,10,Fpolls at the moment.
OL,12,FThe council is already under no
OL,13,Foverall control and, if the Tories
OL,14,Flose their small lead, complex
OL,15,Fcoalition negotiations are likely that
OL,16,Fcould take days to conclude.
OL,18,FBut make no mistake, those stories
OL,19,Fwill likely be secondary to the main
OL,20,Fnarrative of the night - the decline
OL,21,Fof Labour's position in the region.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G7/8
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
